When working with articles in the learn section:

1. Frontmatter Requirements:
```yaml
---
title: "Article Title with Proper Capitalization"
date: YYYY-MM-DD
description: "One-sentence summary of the article content"
topics: ["Topic1", "Topic2"]
difficulty: ["Beginner"|"Intermediate"|"Advanced"]
draft: false
---
```

2. Article Structure:
- Start with H1 title matching the frontmatter title
- Include a 1-2 paragraph introduction below the title
- Use H2 (##) for main sections
- Use H3 (###) for subsections
- Include "What You'll Learn" section after introduction
- Include "Prerequisites" section if applicable
- End with "Summary" and "Related Articles" sections

3. Content Formatting:
- Use bullet points for lists
- Use numbered lists for sequential steps/instructions
- Include code blocks with proper syntax highlighting
- Use tables for comparing data/concepts
- Include relevant cross-links to other articles

4. Technical Elements:
- Format code examples in appropriate language blocks
- Use tables for structured data comparison
- Format links as [Title](mdc:path/to/article)
- Keep headings in proper hierarchical order (H1 > H2 > H3)

5. Educational Style:
- Break complex concepts into digestible sections
- Include practical examples where possible
- Define technical terms when first used
- Use consistent terminology throughout
- Progress from basic to advanced concepts

6. Cross-Referencing:
- Link to related articles in the same difficulty level
- Link to prerequisites when needed
- Use relative paths for internal links
- Include 2-3 related articles at the bottom
